      "rationale": "Three-level mesh refinement study performed on the non-cannulated screw-rod construct. Construct stiffness QoI changed by 3.1% between medium and fine mesh; yield force QoI changed by 2.4%. Richardson extrapolation applied to estimate asymptotic discretization error. Final mesh (approximately 420,000 elements, predominantly hex-dominant C3D8I) selected as production mesh."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Solver residuals and energy balance monitored; iterative convergence confirmed for each load step.",
      "rationale": "Nonlinear static analyses used Newton-Raphson iteration with force residual tolerance 1e-4. Energy balance checked at each load step. No divergence events observed across the 11-specimen ensemble. Contact penetration monitored and confirmed below 0.01 mm throughout loading."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Analysis procedures documented in a controlled simulation plan reviewed by an independent analyst.",
      "rationale": "Simulation plan document (SP-2023-001) reviewed and approved by an independent senior analyst not involved in model construction. Boundary conditions, material assignments, and load application procedures verified against the simulation plan prior to production runs. No use errors identified during review."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Continuum mechanics assumptions (linear elasticity for titanium alloy, large-deformation kinematics, frictional contact) justified for the loading regime and validated against experimental observations.",
      "rationale": "Titanium alloy (Ti-6Al-4V) modeled as bilinear isotropic hardening elastoplastic material consistent with ASTM F136 coupon data. Large-deformation kinematics (NLGEOM ON) enabled. Frictional contact (mu=0.2) applied at screw-rod and rod-set-screw interfaces, consistent with published tribological data for titanium-on-titanium. Model form assumptions corroborated by agreement between predicted and observed deformation patterns in high-speed video from Lab 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties and geometric inputs traceable to measured data; input uncertainty characterised.",
      "rationale": "Elastic modulus (114 GPa) and yield strength (880 MPa) sourced from ASTM F136 coupon tests on production-lot material. Geometric dimensions taken from CMM measurements of three production screws (mean ± 1 SD reported). Input uncertainty propagated through the model using a Monte Carlo approach with 200 replications; 95th-percentile QoI spread reported alongside point-estimate predictions."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test specimens drawn from production lots; dimensional conformance verified by CMM prior to testing.",
      "rationale": "N=11 non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs drawn from three production lots. CMM dimensional inspection confirmed all specimens within drawing tolerances. Lot traceability documented in test reports TR-LAB1-2022 and TR-LAB2-2022. No specimens excluded post-test."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions span the range of COU loading scenarios or deviations from COU conditions are bounded and justified.",
      "rationale": "Testing performed under a single ASTM F1717 standard test condition (10 mm offset, 5 mm/min displacement rate, ambient temperature). The COU encompasses only this standardized test configuration; however, the achieved level is assessed as Gradation 2 because only one test condition was evaluated, limiting the ability to characterize condition-dependent model behavior. This shortfall is documented as an accepted limitation consistent with the regulatory submission scope."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Model inputs mapped directly to measured experimental parameters; any unmeasured inputs identified and their influence bounded.",
      "rationale": "All model boundary conditions (fixture geometry, offset distance, loading rate) mapped directly to measured experimental parameters reported in test reports. Polyaxial screw head engagement torque not measured experimentally; sensitivity of QoIs to this parameter evaluated and found to produce less than 1.5% QoI variation over the plausible torque range, confirming negligible influence."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric (E/uval) computed for each QoI; all metrics satisfy E/uval < 1.96.",
      "rationale": "E/uval computed for construct stiffness (0.87), yield force (1.12), and force at 40 mm displacement (1.34). All three metrics satisfy the pre-specified acceptance criterion of E/uval < 1.96. Percentage differences (4.3%, 7.1%, 5.8%) also satisfy the secondary criterion of less than 10%. Validation comparison plots provided in Appendix C of the credibility assessment report."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
